Key Match Events: The Boston Celtics dominated the Houston Rockets despite missing key players Jaylen Brown and Al Horford.
The Houston Rockets were without Jabari Smith Jr. due to a fractured hand sustained during practice.
Others: Jabari Smith Jr. will be out for 1 to 2 months after fracturing his left hand.
Following the defeat against the Celtics, the Houston Rockets maintain a record of 22-12 but remain in 3rd place in the Western Conference.
